 style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and Consultant level</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> roles. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">It would be helpful for Government to encourage and provide support for links with the Health </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Service and Universities to  provide internships or run-through training to encourage retention of women graduates or PhD students in STEM careers.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Declaration of interests</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">I am a Consultant Clinical Scientist in Microbiology at North Bristol</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> NHS Trust.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">My career path is: BSC in Microbiology from University of Bristol 1977, PhD in Medical Microbiology University of London 1981, Membership of the Royal College of Pathologists (by examination) in 1987, Fellowship of the Royal College of Pathologists in 199</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">My role as a Consultant Clinical Scientist is very similar to that of my medically trained colleagues in providing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> clinical advic</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e on the diagnosis, treatment and management of patients in Primary and Secondary</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> care and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">liaison bet</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ween the Microbiology </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">laboratory and clinicians.  There was no training programme at the time of my training so I have</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> recently </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">been closely involved with the Royal College of Pathologists and with colleagues have developed a Higher Specialist Training curriculum and programme </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to enable more scientists to achieve this especially as medically trained microbiologists training and roles become more clinically ‘hands-on’.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">I believe that the Clinical Scientist role is an excellent career path for women in Microbiology and it is very </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">important that training posts </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are financially supported by the Department of Health.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">I think the skills a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">cquired by wo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">men in this training such as high level expert knowledge of clinical microbiology, clinical liaison with all grades of staff and also incl</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">uding patients and carers, and health service management would transfer very well to other employment sectors so retention of highly trained and skilled women in academic or health service careers is paramount. To do this I believe more support is needed a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">t all levels by employers and at Government level to provide continuing management training and allowing continuing career-long knowledge and skills acquisition in non training senior and Consultant level roles</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to ensure </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> can compete with men for the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">highest level roles. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">It may be there is currently a lack of knowledge in Science graduates and PhD students of the reality of a career in the health service and it would be helpful for Government to encourage and provide support for links with </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the Health</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Service and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Universities to  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">provide internships or run-through training to encourage retention of women graduates or PhD students in STEM careers.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>